PlugwiseOnLinux :

This version pairs your Plugwise Circles and Circle+ on Linux. 

For the moment, this version pairs sockets with identity "000D6F00003". 
It works on firmwares 2008-03-10 (Circle+) and 2008-08-26 (USB stick).

Cloning :

git clone git://github.com/hackstuces/PlugOnLinux.git
cd PlugOnLinux 
git submodule init
git submodule update

Configuring :

run the command : apt-get install python-serial
put the files CrcMoose.py CrcMoose.pyc pol_ap_en.py in the same folder

Using :

go to the folder PlugOnLinux and run : python pol_ap_en.py

Notes :

The pairing is done only when your sockets are initialized. To initialize, connect your Circle during 3s and then disconnect it during 3s. Repeat it 3 times. 


